message.content:
The gas mileage of a vehicle is usually represented in miles per gallon (mpg). To calculate it, simply divide the total distance traveled by the number of gallons used.

For example, if you drove 300 miles and used 10 gallons of fuel:
Gas Mileage = Total Distance Traveled / Number of Gallons Used
Gas Mileage = 300 miles รท 10 gallons
Gas Mileage = 30 mpg
